<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES synthesis theory books]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10529&amp;p=118571#p118571"><![CDATA[
NES sound hardware does not have anything special or unique to write theory books. It is just pair of digital pulse wave generators, triangle wave generator, LFSR for noise, and DPCM unit (this one is relatively unique). The same things are found all around, in old sound chips, old and modern analog or digital or software synthesizers, etc.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Mon Sep 23, 2013 2:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
